# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# gitstate — local-first desktop app configuration (all optional).
#
# gitstate runs on YOUR machine: it reads your git + forge locally, classifies
# locally, and stores locally (SQLite). There is NO server to configure, no
# database URL, no auth secret. Every value below has a sane default; set only
# what you want to override.
#
# Copy to `.env` (or `.env.dev`). Vite reads this file (envDir points at the
# repo root) and exposes only `VITE_*` to the browser; everything else is read
# by the Rust daemon/CLI process.
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Daemon bind (headless peer / `gitstate serve`) ──
# The daemon serves web/dist + the JSON API on this address. The Tauri desktop
# app ignores these and uses an ephemeral loopback port instead.
GITSTATE_ADDR=127.0.0.1
GITSTATE_PORT=7473

# ── Data directory ──
# Where the SQLite database (gitstate.db) and caches live. Defaults to the
# per-OS app-data dir (e.g. ~/Library/Application Support/gitstate on macOS,
# ~/.local/share/gitstate on Linux). Uncomment to override.
# GITSTATE_DATA_DIR=/absolute/path/to/gitstate-data

# ── Static web app ──
# The built React app the daemon serves at `/`. Auto-detected next to the
# binary and in the working directory; override if it lives elsewhere.
# GITSTATE_WEB_DIST=/absolute/path/to/web/dist

# ── Local classification (LLM) ──
# Classification stays LOCAL for privacy. Point at any OpenAI-compatible
# endpoint — llmux, a local model server, etc. If none is set, gitstate uses a
# deterministic keyword/path heuristic (no network) instead.
# VULOS_LLMUX_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8080/v1     # preferred (vulos llmux gateway)
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:11434/v1    # fallback (any OpenAI-compatible)
# VULOS_LLMUX_API_KEY=...                       # if your endpoint needs a key
# OPENAI_API_KEY=...
# GITSTATE_CLASSIFY_MODEL=llama3.1              # model name to request

# ── Forge access (GitHub / GitLab) ──
# gitstate prefers your local `gh` / `glab` CLI (already authenticated). Set a
# token only if you don't have the CLI installed and want the REST/GraphQL path.
# First match wins for each forge.
# GITSTATE_GH_TOKEN=ghp_...     # or: GH_TOKEN / GITHUB_TOKEN
# GITSTATE_GLAB_TOKEN=glpat-... # or: GITLAB_TOKEN

# ── Signed taxonomy (advanced) ──
# The category taxonomy is a signed data file embedded in the app. Override the
# doc or the pinned public key only if you run your own signed taxonomy.
# GITSTATE_TAXONOMY_PATH=/absolute/path/to/taxonomy.json
# GITSTATE_TAXONOMY_PUBKEY=<64-hex-ed25519-pubkey>

# ── Frontend dev (Vite) ──
# During `npm run dev` (web/), the dev server proxies /api + /health to a
# locally-run `gitstated` on GITSTATE_PORT. Only VITE_* vars reach the browser.
# VITE_APP_NAME=gitstate
